{ Why 1.e4? At master level, 1.e4 is the most popular first move. White controls the center, opens the diagonal for his light-squared bishop  (bringing himself one step closer to castling)  , and prepares to start developing. 1.e4 has been the favorite of many world champions and amateurs alike. One key aspect of 1.e4 compared to other popular first moves such as 1.d4 is that the resulting positions tend to be a bit more open, and there are fewer transpositions to other openings. }
