{ White develops his knight to the natural c3-square, asking Black what he wants to do next. }
3... dxe4
{ The Rubinstein variation. Black gives opens the a8-h1 diagonal at the cost of increasing White's space advantage. }
4. Nxe4 { White recaptures the pawn. } 4... Nd7
{ Black prepares to play ...Nf6 because 4...Nf6 5.Nxf6+ forces Black's queen out prematurely or doubles Black's pawns. It should be noted that Black can also go for a quiet setup with ...Bd7 followed by ...Bc6  (Fort Knox Variation)  , a plan that will be explored in the main chapter. }
