9... a6
{ Black controls the b5-square  (Nb5 is prevented)  and intends on following up with ...Qc7 and ...b5. }
10. Bb3
{ White usually meets ...a6 with Bb3 in order to not lose a tempo after Black plays ...b5 or ...Ne5. }
10... Qc7 { Black prepares to play ...b5 by protecting his c6-knight. } 11.
Rhg1
